        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "describing",
          "value": "The structure `Diffeomorph` (notation `≃ₘ^n`) bundles a bijection (via `Equiv`) with smoothness of both the map and its inverse, directly formalizing the definition of diffeomorphism.",
          "format": "text/plain"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Diffeomorphism?oldid=1351444286",
        "selector": {
          "type": "TextQuoteSelector",
          "exact": "is a diffeomorphism if it is a bijection and its inverse",
          "prefix": "continuously differentiable map ",
          "suffix": " is differentiable as well. If t"
        }
      }
    },
